reply.p: The information requested (where available) has been placed in the House Libraries.

I refer to the Answer given in the House of Commons on 14 July by the Financial Secretary (Mr Healey) to the honourable Member for Epsom and Ewell (Mr Grayling) (column 1168W), which records the totals paid including VAT to Exchequer Partnership plc, Partnerships UK plc and Robson Associates in 2004-05. In each case a list of every item of goods or services purchased could be assembled only at disproportionate cost.
